TITLE: 'A lot of people quit a job with the intent to take some time off': Here's how to financially prepare
SUMMARY: Before you quit your job, remember that until you find your next one, you'll still have to cover regular expenses and health insurance.

TITLE: Two-year-old events start-up Hopin boomed in the pandemic. Now it's a $7.75 billion business
SUMMARY: Virtual events start-up Hopin had only eight employees in March 2020; its headcount now stands at 800.

TITLE: Judge denies Elizabeth Holmes' request to suppress patient complaints about Theranos
SUMMARY: The federal judge also denied Holmes' request to exclude filings from a regulatory report by the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services.

TITLE: Bitcoin vs. gold: Here’s what billionaire Ray Dalio thinks
SUMMARY: Why billionaire Ray Dalio would choose buying gold over bitcoin.

TITLE: Most of America's extra savings during the pandemic are going to the wealthy
SUMMARY: While it's not surprising that America's savings, like income and wealth, are concentrated at the top, the degree of the savings inequality was unexpected.

TITLE: Here's how much 2021 winners of Mega Millions and Powerball have forked over in taxes
SUMMARY: Between the Powerball and Mega Millions jackpots that have been claimed so far this year, winners have paid more than $500 million in federal taxes.

TITLE: Billionaire Ray Dalio: The most successful people are ‘by and large’ better at doing this one thing
SUMMARY: Billionaire investor Ray Dalio says successful people are 'by and large' better at recognizing and understanding their weaknesses than an average person.

TITLE: Bill Gates and Melinda French Gates are officially divorced following 27-year marriage
SUMMARY: Bill and Melinda French Gates were one of the most prominent couples in business. A push for divorce came after reports of Bill Gates' ties to Jeffrey Epstein.

TITLE: NBA legend Charles Barkley: My advisors 'don't believe in crypto'
SUMMARY: NBA legend Charles Barkley says his financial advisors are not believers in cryptocurrency, plus he reveals the biggest lesson he's learned about money.

TITLE: Google founders have sold $1 billion in stock since May, the most since 2017
SUMMARY: Larry Page and Sergey Brin last sold shares in 2017, when their last plan expired. Since then, the stock price has nearly tripled.

TITLE: Missing Japan? Virtual tours come with shopping, drinks and souvenirs
SUMMARY: Tourist attractions and enterprising tour guides are using technology to emulate the look, feel and taste of a trip to Japan.

SUMMARY: Bill Hwang's nonprofit saw its assets jump by over $100 million just two years prior his office set off a market meltdown.

SUMMARY: "It's a long time ago I heard someone say that," Dutch teen Oliver Daemen says Jeff Bezos responded when he told him he'd never shopped on Amazon. But there's a reason for that.

TITLE: NYC mayoral race favorite Eric Adams privately seeks partnerships with business leaders
SUMMARY: Eric Adams' outreach comes after years of battles between Mayor Bill de Blasio and the New York business community.

TITLE: Elizabeth Warren makes fresh push for wealth tax – 'Yes, Jeff Bezos, I'm looking at you'
SUMMARY: Sen. Elizabeth Warren reignited her push for a tax on the accumulated wealth of the richest Americans by pointing at the Amazon founder.

TITLE: Hobby Lobby's $1.6 million Gilgamesh tablet has been forfeited to the U.S.

TITLE: NBA legend Charles Barkley: ‘The only people who are not vaccinated are just a--holes'
SUMMARY: NBA legend Charles Barkley on whether sports leagues should require athletes to get vaccinated.

TITLE: Many states are holding lotteries with cash or other prizes to boost vaccination rates. Here's how much winners could owe in taxes
SUMMARY: Whether cash or another type of prize, the IRS expects winners of any lottery to pay taxes on the value of their jackpots.

SUMMARY: "It's a long shot, it stresses me out in terms of how to get there," Google CEO Sundar Pichai says of the company's climate change goals.

SUMMARY: The University of Exeter is offering students who want to study medicine a £10,000 ($13,735) bursary and free first-year accommodation to defer their place.

TITLE: Everything you always wanted to know about yachting, but were too afraid to ask
SUMMARY: CNBC spoke with several yacht owners who agreed to answer all questions — with no topics off limits.

SUMMARY: "It’s possible to make very, extremely safe nuclear," Elon Musk said at The B-Word conference hosted by the Crypto Council for Innovation.

TITLE: IRS estimates of unpaid taxes are 'unfounded,' says Rep. Kevin Brady
SUMMARY: IRS Commissioner Charles Rettig testified before Congress in April that the "tax gap" -- or amount of taxes owed that go unpaid each year -- could be as high as $1 trillion.

SUMMARY: "Anything that looks good and feels good" is art, Damien Hirst told CNBC on Wednesday. "It doesn't have to be in a gallery."

TITLE: Fintech keeps minting billionaires as Robinhood co-founders prepare for massive IPO
SUMMARY: Based on the middle of Robinhood's expected IPO price range provided on Monday, co-founders Vlad Tenev and Baiju Bhatt each own stakes worth about $2.6 billion.

TITLE: Robinhood CEO Vlad Tenev could be worth $2.5 billion after IPO
SUMMARY: Robinhood CEO and co-founder Vlad Tenev will have a paper fortune of over $2.5 billion when the company starts trading, according to an SEC filing.
